ype":"text","text":" delegate) to send feedback to Openpath. This feature should be used for development, testing and integration purposes only"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Feature: added "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"onMotionStatusChanged"},{"type":"text","text":" delegate to report motion status changed"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Feature: added ","type":"text"},{"code":"enableErrorNotificationsForItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to enable\/disable error notifications for an entry or reader.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Improvement: all unlock responses (now including Wave) will be reported via a new delegate function ","type":"text"},{"code":"onUnlockResponse","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Improvement: our SDK and its dependencies are now distributed using binary frameworks so that the same frameworks can be used across simulator, device, and different Swift & XCode versions. This change will also remove the need to use CocoaPods for our SDK dependencies."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Improvement: beacon region monitoring reduced from 20 to 10 regions so that 10 are free for your use (Apple allows a max limit of 20 regions per app)","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Migration Guide","anchor":"Migration-Guide"},{"type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Use binary frameworks","anchor":"Use-binary-frameworks"},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Adding the framework","anchor":"Adding-the-framework"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remove the old version of our SDK from your project. Copy the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"frameworks"},{"type":"text","text":" directory  (provided with our new SDK) to your project. From your Xcode project root, go to the "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"General"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" tab, under "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Embedded Libraries","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":", click on the + button. Browse to the frameworks directory (the one that we just added) and select the entire list of frameworks, then verify that under the column "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Embed"},{"type":"text","text":" all the frameworks are set as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Embed & Sing"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Upgrade to New Build System","anchor":"Upgrade-to-New-Build-System"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you were using "},{"code":"Legacy Build System","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", you need to upgrade to "},{"code":"New Build System","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" because the legacy system doesn’t support Binary Frameworks. Please go to File-> Workspace Settings (or Project Settings if you’re not in a workspace), and select "},{"code":"New Build System","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for both Shared Workspace & Per-User Workspace Settings."}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Remove CocoaPods","anchor":"Remove-CocoaPods"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you were using the [CocoaPods][3] Engine just for the purpose of installing dependencies for our SDK, here is a guide to remove it from you project:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["sudo gem install cocoapods-deintegrate cocoapods-clean","pod deintegrate","pod cache clean --all","rm Podfile"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"NOTE: Thanks to [Haiyesbye][1] for his post on [Medium][2].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"[1]: https:\/\/medium.com\/@haiyesbye\/remove-uninstall-deintegrate-cocoapods-from-your-xcode-ios-project-c4621cee5e42) “Haiyesbye”"},{"type":"text